Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic and topological investigations of ternary mixtures with o-toluidine, tetrahydropyran, and picolines: Excess molar volume and excess isentropic compressibility
Citation.sAbstract: The density and speed of sound ternary {o-toluidine (i) + tetrahydropyran (j) + alpha-, beta-, or gamma-picoline (k)} mixtures have been measured over the entire composition range at T = (298.15, 303.15, and 308.15) K. The excess molar volume and excess isentropic compressibility values of the mixtures have been predicted by using the experimental results. The observed thermodynamic properties have been fitted to Redlich-Kister equation to determine ternary adjustable parameters and standard deviations. The excess molar volume and excess isentropic compressibility values have also been analyzed in terms of (1) Graph theory and (2) Prigogine-Flory-Patterson theory (PFP). It has been observed that excess molar volume and excess isentropic compressibility data determined by Graph theory compare well with experimental values.
